    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.12.7" />
                
                <fw type="curatorial">7</fw>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    <hi rend="caps">CABLE ADDRESS
                        <lb/>
                    BROMASITE, NEW YORK
                    
                    TELEPHONES
                        <lb/>
                    VANDERBILT 2792-3-4-5-6
                    
                    BRANDT &amp; BRANDT
                        <lb/>
                    BRANDT &amp; KIRKPATRICK.
                        <lb/>
                    101 PARK AVENUE
                        <lb/>
                    NEW YORK</hi>
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>February 2, 1925.</dateline>
                    
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Mr. John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt,</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Branson, Mo.</addrLine>
                    </address>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Mr. Neihardt:-</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I spoke to Mr. Yearsley of the Ritz-Carlton Pictures last week to try to find out whether they were going to exercise their option on "The Song of Three Friends".</p>
                
                <p>He was leaving for the coast the day I telephoned and promised to wire me as soon as he got there what decision the company had made. Of course their option expires on next Friday the sixth, and unles<del>x</del><add>s</add> I hear something by Wednesday night, I shall send them a formal telegram notifying them of the expiration of the option.</p>
                
                <p>Their plans are very indefinite even yet and I am sorry to say I cannot give you any tip as to how the situation is going to break, but I do hope that they will decide on doing the picture. I shall wire you as soon as I hear from them.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Very truly yours,</salute>
                    
                    <signed>Lilla Worthington
                            <unclear>as</unclear>
                    BRANDT &amp; BRANDT.</signed>
                
                    <note>LW:AS</note>
                </closer>
                
                <note type="recipient">Brandt + Brandt on <hi rend="underline">The Song of Three Friends</hi></note>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
